reviews.text: Made a thirty min trip to try this location and it was def worth it. The waitress, Phoenix, was phenomenal! We also loved all of our food. The Mediterranean burger with lamb was such great combination of flavors. We shared the pancakes and French toast because our six year old couldn’t finish it. We had plenty of leftovers. My husband ordered the egg and cheddar burger and said it was pretty good. I loved the art and the vibe of the place. We arrived around 1030 and there was barely anyone there on Sunday. But literally when we left at 1120, the entire building seemed packed to capacity. Glad we came early for brunch! Well, three locations down and plenty more to try. This chain has a reputation of having great quality food, drinks, art, books and id family friendly. But could be great for a group of friends or lover.

A great birthday dinner! The food was good and well suited for lots of different dietary preferences. It was busy, so service was a little slow, but very friendly! Only real complaint is the drinks — although cheaper than most DC cocktails they were also a little underwhelming.

My food and drink were delicious!!! The service, however, was pretty good...once I was actually severed. LOL I waited a long time after being seated. A couple seated after me was served before me. My server had to be told to come to my table and she barely checked on me. She apologized so it made me feel a little better, but I'm definitely expecting stellar service my next visit. Also, they have a nice bookstore! I forgot to take a picture of the carrot cake I took to go. It was so good!

I loved the food here so much, I came back the next day at a different  location. They didn't disappoint, but I wasn't able to get the vegan lovers pasta that made me want to come back just because it's only available after 3pm
I ended up getting a black bean burger, and another pomegranate lemonade with fries. This was good too but that pasta will be what brings me back a third time for sure. My daughter felt the same way about the vegan cheesecake. She bought one to go just because it was so delicious.
I definitely recommend all vegans and non-vegans eat here. They really had something for everyone.

When you visit places like this , it feels wrong that you can give it only 5 stars. I would give this place an entire constellation for the amazing atmosphere , great food, a mix of people enjoying the moment. The combination with food, drinks, art, photos and books makes this place a heaven on earth. Great service. If poetry had a place this would be the right one. If you live in Dc or you simply are visiting make this place a priority for your meals or just for a drink with your friends. Great job guys for this extraordinary concept
Great bar with good prices on drinks and food. Outdoor seating is plentiful.

Went here for happy hour, was disappointed with the deals, they only offer $1 off beers which was disappointing.
Ordered an orange crush which didn't taste like an orange crush (used orange juice).
Ambience was nice and a lot of seating.

Decent enough food, but it’s overshadowed by their slow, inattentive service.  It takes at least 4 employees to take care of one order.  20+ minutes until you’ll receive a can of beer. And nobody even brought out the check.
Nice mix of relaxed or high-energy moods, depending on where in the bar you are. The upstairs is fun but potentially treacherous, what with all the flailing and feral youths

This is the whitest bar in the universe. The music here tastes like raisans in potato salad. This is where high school teachers in Disney Channel Original movies would go to after work. Three tracks of their playlist is enough to make you feel the melanin leaving your soul. This bar got an 800 credit score. This is the Wayne's Brothers parody of a white hipster bar. Stay here too long you will spontaneously start calling people "brah." Fun for going on safari to check out how the sunducker crowd lives but not worth more than a gimmicky night out. 3 tuna casseroles out of five.

Had a lunch meeting here with a colleague and was really hoping to each lunch. However, I was told that the restaurant didn’t carry mustard which was a bummer. I got the banana nut muffin instead and it was really good. Tryst definitely has the sweets down. My  Golden Milk latte was really really good as well. My colleague, who’s a regular here, ordered an iced latte with lavender which he really enjoyed. Personally, this is a spot for hot or iced bevs and pastries, but the food menu left much to be desired.

Great spot.

Went here for the first time at night after dinner. We got tea and a slice of Carrot Cake. All was good.

The interior is really nice. Super 90’s cafe vibes. I will for sure come back to work as there is ample space and multiple types of seating (coaches, two-tops, counter).

The staff is super friendly and overall it was a great ending to a good evening.

Cute place with great coffee & a limited menu. Unfortunately, our visit was painfully SLOW. Sat at the counter, it took 15 min for someone to take our order & another 10 to get coffee. Had to walk over to our server and ask him for a to go box & our check, we could have easily just walked out...no one was tracking anything there & I'm guessing it happens. Lox & Cream Cheese Everything Bagel was good, heavy on the lox & red onions, the lemon cream cheese & the bagel itself were very good.

My sister and I popped into Tryst in the evening for hot chocolate and carrot cake (which were both huge and tasted great). It's wonderful to have a place to go in the evening that's not a bar, even though they do serve alcohol. Service is also prompt and digital, with dine in or take out options. One of my favorite places in DC!
Very nice atmosphere. I had Turkey Club Wrap with chips. It was good, I would appreciate more seasoning either in the Wrap or on the meat. All over a great experience.

A classic lunch counter in the heart of DC! Right across the street from the U street metro station on the yellow/green line. Fast, friendly service. Counter order and then seat yourself. The meal combo deal is an extra $5 for a fountain drink and fries. I recommend skipping it because it's not quite worth it. Spend the money on a milkshake instead! The walls are filled with pictures famous people who have eaten there. This place is great! Definitely check it out.

Walk in and order, they will bring you your food.  There are a few tables up front, in the middle and in the back.  Pictures of famous people all over the walls.  Even have a TV playing with more pictures.  This is a DC landmark.

The place is fun to check out.  But the chili was just ok...

Service was good.

This is one of the best hot dogs I have ever had. I ended up getting 2 of them. They are on the pricier side, but they are worth it. They come with chili of you choose to get that as a topping. The hot dogs that ended up getting were all beef. One set of fries is all you need. There's also a place right next door that they own that has some really good cheap drinks. Great spot.

I was told that a visit to DC is MUST include the Original Ben's Chili Bowl on U street in the Shaw neighborhood of DC.

What I learned is that Ben’s is not just a minority owned restaurant, it is a civil rights landmark. Stepping into Ben’s is looking back at a glimpse of history and feeling the sense of community it built.

Like a museum, Ben’s walls are adorned with framed photographs, of founders, Virginia and her late husband, Ben, taken throughout the past 60 years; or photographs of famous visitors. You can even sit at the table Barack Obama sat!

The staff were welcoming, patient and personable. I’m not a big chili or hot dog eater but they took the time to explain the menu to me and recommended items, even though it was very busy.

They also have vegan and gluten free options.

The place is not small, but, it will fill a bit like that at Fridays and Saturdays night as in the middle of the bar and club zone, along with its tourist popularity because Obama was there (along with some other celebrities).

They say they have parking at the back, I did not do much to find it as I already have parked my car somewhere else.

The food is very good if not great, it feels of good quality and fresh, with obviously a great and original flavour. Even though, the price is low, I would say the portions are small too, so consider this when ordering so you take two hamburger instead of one!!!

The people working in there is friendly, however, it looks they are overworked and not organized, making the service to be slow and giving a somewhat bad experience because they tend to forget orders (they forgot mine twice).

Overall good place to have dinner after a long day of walking and visiting museums or to have something in your stomach just before starting the party or after it.

Lovely friendly place for breakfast. Food was tasty and the coffee great. We loved our time here. We will be back x highly recommend.. we did come back for the evening menu.. lovely chips an I had the lemonade which was lovely xx

The interior design and the outdoor seating are fantastic. It is clean and each table has enough room. It is a dog friendly restaurant described in Google map’s reviews, so we came here on Saturday morning. The waiter who assigned us a table in the outdoor seating was very nice and friendly, but unfortunately, the one who served us was less friendly. I would have gave five stars if he could be a little bit more friendly. I asked water for my dog and he seems not willing to do so. There were other dogs in the restaurant and they all got clean water and nicer water bowl. My dog Lucky did not have that privilege, unfortunately. I ordered Coupe Royale and it was great. The chicken sausages and hashbrown square are recommended. The latte art and animal crackers are cute.

This was one of my friend’s favorite place and i’m glad i was able to stop by. They serve breakfast all day!! The menu has a lot of different options including vegetarian and vegan. Service was great and the food was good too. Solid choice for breakfast and lunch.

Awesome neighborhood modern diner. Can be busy during peak brunch hours but everything I’ve tried here is delicious.

Can also walk in for quick coffee/pastry.

When you walk in you’ll see a pic of Obama having a meal 🍽 at the Coupe. When you have your first meal there then you’ll understand why he was there.

This restaurant is great food, friendly staff, good vibes all around. I like to go here for breakfast 🧇 ☕️ sometimes and I live all the way in Maryland and it’s in D.C, that should say enough.

Prob the best time I had in DC was at this place, super dive and by dive I mean no disrespect, just a cool place that had a killer playlist and good cheap drinks! Great place whether you go with someone, a group, or solo... you're gonna be there and have fun and meet people... mixed crowded, young and old...

Great bar with rooftop vibes - but the rooftop is not an open ceiling but the lighting and height of the ceiling gives that same airy feeling. Dive bar, good for big groups. The downstairs is even good for a date as it’s kind of tight near the window.

Though we enjoyed the vibe here, and the cool beer selection, doesn't seem like this is where you come for yummy, homemade food. I ordered a BBQ bacon cheeseburger.. the presentation was cool, but it was pretty overcooked and lacked any seasoning, even with me specifically asking if they can season it.
Instead, I ended up with some very less than appetizing looking chicken tenders. The fries were pretty tasty.

Great local bar with large variety of cocktails and beer.

Roof deck is open and has even more seating

The prices are super low and and it's great neighborhood dive bar with a great vibe

Great ambiance, good deals (shout out to Paul Rudd Wednesdays), not to mention a unique variety of drinks (e.g. lychee jelly sake). Also, the rooftop is the only place I know of in DC where you can smoke.

Their new trivia is fun too, especially if you’re sick of TriviaMatic questions and need a change.

The food is pretty good. I like their orange chicken. And I am a fan of egg rolls.
And the ppl are friendly.
Decent food at a great price. It would be better if they have a better interior design.

I had orange chicken as my husband encouraged me to try it, it was delicious, price is reasonable (you get a good size portion for little money).

I will definitely eat food from here again.

Let me just say and I’m from Tiktok I’m also a black women . Des needs to be fired . She was mad or jealous that the manager took his order and didn’t go through the line with the employees but thought she was above the manager . It’s disrespectful & she did way to much . Hopefully she got fired because panda don’t need a black women working here who can’t control herself . 🤷🏾‍♀️

Good food - bad portions.

I think it depends on the time of day you go, but i've been here around 12pm, 3pm, and 7pm - and it's always been the same. They skimp out on portions as if you aren't overpaying already for a plate of food. There's also a huge cleanliness issue with the tables and the refreshments area.

Food is good! Just the portions and cleanliness needs to be resolved.

tl;dr: Subpar falafel bowl, but amazing fries and curry ketchup & long service time for "fast food".

Falafel Bowl - 3/5: Falafel was kinda dry, and also drenched in sauce. The pickles and other toppings were not bad, but I couldn't shake the feeling that other established chains just do it better for bigger portions.

Fries - 5/5: These steak fries were delicious and perfectly fried and crispy even after my drive home as a takeout order. And I wasn't expecting the ketchup to elevate the fries to a whole new level. I'm glad I took the recommendations to get fries at a falafel shop! I would go back just for the fries.

Service - 3/5: Just felt like the cashier didn't want to be there and it was very quiet. They blocked off where the food is assembled due to covid, which is acceptable, but I wish I could see my bowl being assembled and seeing the toppings instead of just hoping they were good enough. Also there was only 1 person in front of me, and it took what felt like 15-20 minutes to complete my order. I was looking for something quicker.

Quirky spot with good falafels.

I was looking for a light, refreshing meal on a Tuesday night. This place didn’t disappoint.

The falafel bowl with everything was good. A bit pricey considering the size of the bowl, but quality over quantity.

The fries were a bit meh. It comes with curry ketchup which is an interesting twist. A pleasant surprise.

Overall, a good place for a light meal. The interior decor is unique. It’s worth stopping by.

It was fine, but just fine. Falafel Inc is way better in terms of overall flavor, and the sauces they provide are way better, but this shop excels in all the free toppings so it's a good go to for quantity, but not quality.

I got the regular falafel sandwich loaded with hummus, baba ganoush, pickled cauliflower, pickled cabbage, tahini, and the red pepper sauce. It was a formidable creation but just lacking any standout flavor.

Their fries were just fries, and I didn't find the curry ketchup anything to write home about.

Friendly service, and great decor. Love the Amsterdam style, including all the old school music call outs including the Fugazi poster.

Oh, and they really want you to mask here, and have lots of funny signs to remind you.

A bite to remember!
I’m a big fan of falafel, and here was just great! Price is reasonable and u have many great choice to add to your falafel with no extra charge.
Also it’s located in one of the coolest street of dc occupied with bars, cafe n restaurants.

When I was in town and looking for sone quick lunch options and wanted to have veg thus when found this place. Got to see many accolades from different journals saying this is one of the best falafel place.. I took falafel sandwich and my friend took falafel bowl. The pita bread was soft , falafel was flavorful and their tahini tastes so yumm .. I would definitely recommend this place though inside theres not much place to sit however they’ve outside sitting area as well

name: WOW Café
vicinity: Mordecai Johnson Administration Building, 2400 6th Street Northwest, Washington

reviews.text: Terrible customer service. Food is just okay.

I order Angelico if I don’t want to drive to Pete’s, but that doesn’t mean they’re quicker. I ordered at 5:15 this afternoon. At 5:35 I got an email saying the pizza was “out for delivery.”  Nothing arrived in 40 minutes so I called. “Don’t know why you got that email, the delivery guy is just waiting for one more pizza and he’ll leave.”  5 minutes later, a knock on the door with the pizza. Stone cold.  I’m guessing the email was right and the delivery guy forgot. I think I’ll drive to Pete’s next time.

Customer service needs major improvement. I was giving old pizza, the sauce was already dried up. Decided to try it but was horrible. If you're going to sell slices have some made in a rotating display and not try and make a buck with stale pizza.
My family orders pizza from here quite often as we live nearby.  I have to say the pizza is very yummy. Also the service is good and I would recommend.

I ordered from this place for the first time and really enjoyed it. The reviews made me a little concerned but I am glad I did not listen. I ordered a large portobello mushroom and it was enough for my boyfriend and I. The pizza was very good and the feta on it really pulled the entire pizza together. Usually I prefer my pizzas with red sauce but the veggie ingredients and garlic and herb truly made it very flavorful. I did do pick up so by the time I made it home it wasn’t as hot but it was still good. I did eat the leftovers the next day and popped it in the oven to get it toasted and it tasted just as good. Definitely will order form here again.
HORRIBLE place, they're running over 5 Ghost kitchens and all orders take 30+ minutes.

Ok breakfast food. Loved the concept of local ingredients though! Nothing taste-wise stood out this visit but it was all good and we would be willing to try other items as the sandwiches next to us looked amazing!

Great local spot for a quick bite, prices pretty average. Atmosphere relaxed.

French toast has chicken served right on top
Of it.  Mushy and lack of flavor in French toast.  Chicken is tender but also flat flavor.  Onion rings are burnt and lack flavor.  Looks like the kind you buy frozen and fry.  Soda machine broken.  Milkshake was delightful, sweet and creamy! All of the tables are peeling finish on wood tops.  The bench seat upholstery is cracked and peeling.  All the vents in the top of the dining room are fuzzy with dusty ick.  The waitress and host are very nice.  Too bad the food isn’t as stellar as it could be, such a good trendy location and updated historic location.
Willy at The Diner was so awesome! Excellent customer service. The fish tacos and cherry blossom shake were amazing! Got a table outside in the shade. Very satisfied, will definitely be back!

I'm a professional hitman and a hearty, nutritious meal is an important part of my regimen. Right up there with cleaning my gun. Anyway, I always stop by The Diner for some good eats and some friendly banter with my fellow hitmen colleagues. Great crowd; nobody likes hanging around with a bunch of stiffs. I always order the Monte Cristo, because who doesn't love a ham and cheese sandwich on French Toast? Yum. Anyway, the waitstaff is great and I love the old style booths. Lots of privacy, which is important in my line of work. 👍

Went to this place while visiting DC with my boyfriend. The food was amazing and the service was even better! Our waitress (wish I could remember her name) was awesome and very accommodating. Will definitely visit again when I’m in DC!

So glad I stumbled upon this little gem of a place. Not fancy, serves beer in jars, and has some killer brisket and pulled pork. This is a great place for work happy hour. Super casual, good food, cool vibe.

Been coming here for almost a decade and couldn't be more glad to have this place in the neighborhood. Okay amount of seating both inside and out, decent staff who are pretty quick and attentive, and delicious swachos (including a vegetarian option). I dig the mason-jar-for-draft vibe too. Note for the sensitive: smoking is permitted on the front patio.

Cool venue and selection of beers but they add gratuity automatically to your check and don't tell you they've done that. When asking the bar tenders about that they pretty much made it clear they expect you to tip on top of the about with the gratuity automatically included.

American Ice was rightfully popular on Saturday night. They have plenty of indoor and outdoor seating options. The prices are reasonable and the drink service was prompt. As a wine enthusiast, I would have preferred to have more options to choose from. The industrial decor and open concept enhance the atmosphere and overall experience at the bar.
The vibe is cool, the service is really bad, the food is mid. It's pretty expensive for what you get, and it's got auto-gratitudy, which isn't very clearly said or labeled anywhere but the receipt

If you looking for the baddest of drag brunches, my b*#%€$ is the baddest. The show kept moving on and the positivity was flowing. The food was good. There’s a portion of the drag that gets emotional and had me crying. It was all love in the drag. Will be going back again. Love is love. We all prosper.

We went to the Drag Brunch today and it was AWESOME! Good food, good drinks, some of the most amazing and charismatic performers I've ever had the pleasure of seeing. The amount of happy energy from the dancers and the audience was even more intoxicating than the alcohol!

I mean, I cried. It was that much of a wonderful time. We went here for Perry’s Drag Brunch (Top Drag Brunch in the Nation by the way) and had theeee Best time!

Food is in a buffet style. Everything was seasoned and tasted amazing. For Brunch (3) ladies performed and the phrase “Take My Money,” will never be the same again. We loved the atmosphere, music, performances, food and everything else.

Come here at LEAST 20 minutes early to find parking. Bring cash or bills to exchange please. Really can’t express how great of a time it was. Awesome staff/management team and really beautiful atmosphere.

I’m definitely going again. Also, Congratulations to the Performers who were celebrating their Birthday and upcoming Wedding, respectively. It was beautiful meeting you all. Encourage anyone and everyone to go.
Value for money. Has a great variety of options, not the highest quality of Japanese food. The Happy hour has great value. Got the Omakase sushi.

Extremely tasty, elegant and not too expensive. Walked in on a Sunday evening, wasn’t expecting much but the place surprised me: it is nice, service was great and everything we ordered, especially the food, was delicious.

A reliable DC rooftop. I’ve been here many many times, sometimes it’s beyond crowded, where it’s uncomfortable and sweaty, and sometimes the mosquitoes can get you up here. But overall a good place to have in the rotation. I was just recently here on a Sunday, ordered a few hookahs, vodka soda $16 here, and they do add a 20% service fee already so that includes the tip. $16 is a lot to me for a very basic drink, but that’s how it goes. The bathroom line is never too bad, and they have a water jug at the bar on all this is a good spot.
Food was good and came out fast, service was ok, drinks eh not that great. You order and pay with your phone btw. Rooftop was too crowded so didn't get to experience it that night

I liked dining here for HH. The jerk chicken tacos and mojitos were good. The waiters are very attentive. While the menu is limited I think it creates better quality small bites. I really liked the buttermilk chicken sandwich, truffle fries and the Ceasar brussel sprouts.

Went for Sunday brunch.  I've never experienced a place where you ordered everything through an app, with limited wait staff engagement. However, our server was very nice and accommodating. They played good music, and served delicious bottomless mimosas.  Seating was kind of close to other guests, whereas there was no privacy; we could hear the guests during next to us whole conversation. Overall the food & vibes were good.

Good Location right on U .. and I like that it’s a rooftop, hip hop music was ok but djs always play the same thing need someone versatility.. PAID 25 dollars per drink then 20% service fee is insane for a small cup !! How high do they think they can keep raising their drink prices.. 2 drinks came to 60 dollars after the fee and tax not worth it very weak and small

Finding a new place to eat is always an adventure in itself. For a late dinner, we chance upon El Chucho. One cannot go wrong with Mexican cuisine. The menu may be short, but the food is good. I enjoyed a fresh vegetarian burrito with cooked mushrooms and peppers. Although the table ordered a side of rice and beans, I was well satiated with the burrito alone. My sisters ordered different taco dishes: one with seasoned chicken and the other a seared Mahi Mahi. The tacos come in a set of two. Although the shells are petite, the tacos are layered well with fresh ingredients.
EL Chucho has a long list of alcoholic concoctions. Additionally, they feature homemade soda ranging from tropical flavors to mixes with spicy pepper notes.
Overall, the restaurant is pleasant to try. They have plenty of outdoor seating.

Come in here for a drink (or as many as you can handle) but also stay here for the food. Awesome tequila and mezcal served by friendly and knowledgeable bartenders. What more could you ask for.

Haven’t had a bad thing on the menu and the food is usually very quick.

Fun neighborhood spot that is now also open late night.

Service was great. I love the overall vibe of the restaurant. The elote and chips and guacamole are really good. My favorite tacos were the pescado tacos (fried salmon). The flavors were perfect. The asada and pollo tacos needed more flavor. I added guacamole and salsa to them and they were better. The drinks are well made and the menu was great. I’d definitely return to try some other menu items!

Video Review -
IG: eatswithchar
TikTok: charlenequeen
The flavours were ok. Tacos are small but filling.  Too much is going on so you lose the taste of the meat it's all condiments and salsas.  Churros are ok a little too soft for my liking.

Just got to DC and decided we want Mexican fare. Looked at the google reviews and listing and found this great hole-in-the -wall.  What a fantastic place!  They have street side seating so we can enjoy the warm weather.  And the food was the best I think I ever had.  I ordered the dinner feature tacos Birria Quesa tacos and they were fantastic.  The flavors and the portion, there were two big stuffed tacos.  The guacamole was outstanding.  I don’t like extra spice and all of the food I chose was packed with flavor.  You will love this place.
Food is delicious!! However, it was hot inside the building. Please improve the air conditioner so it's not so hot inside the building in June.

A beautiful and delicious meal to satisfy a soul food craving. I was a bit shocked when the prices at the grill were way higher than the online menu, but once I got past the shock of being told my total was more than a few dollars higher than I expected and saw the food/thought about supporting a local institution I didn’t really mind. Just look at this photo! You can practically see the crunch and satisfaction.

I have lived in DC since 1980 and this was my first visit to the infamous Florida Avenue Grill. The young lady taking orders was very attentive to our party. Our breakfast was very good. Everything was very tasty. It was a little chilly that day. The stools can use an update. If you can't eat in, they are very good with takeout services. Looking forward to returning.

1st time visit & probably last... I was looking forward to having breakfast at "The World Famous Florida Grill"... As I entered,

1) there was no one to address

2) the service was sub-par...Not friendly at all..

3) The food was not as I ordered... Eggs with cheese was hard scrambled with a slice if cheese on top. My pancakes were not hot & was served with no butter

4) The waitress never "gave" my check but insisted that I walk on the other side of the restaurant to pay my bill...By the way, I never got my itemized bill but she definitely took my credit card without even apologizing...

5) I left there feeling really disappointed & a bit unfulfilled.

Sorry but its my truth!
A Washington, DC institution! I just wish they would bring back the liver & onions to the menu.😁

The best vibe and my favorite restaurant in DC. Brought my family here for my 21st birthday and they had a great time. Happy Hour is well priced and the staff is incredibly helpful and friendly. I look forward to coming back with everyone who comes to visit me in DC or just for a good time out. Highly recommend!

Came for a late night drink and wasn't denied. Not only that, felt at home and the service was fair. Great, but when I say fair, I was treated like a patron and not a dollar. Thanks to Pablo for serving a great drink and I told him to give me what he thought was the best margarita in the house... had the nerve to serve me freaking Topaz!!! But it was AWESOME! THANKS FOR A GREAT EXPERIENCE 🙂

LOVED IT HERE. The vibes are immaculate it's a very fun atmosphere and the kitchen is open late. The service is extremely quick, the drinks are great, and the prices are good. I had the Miami Vice Daquiri and it was as thick as a smoothie. The enchiladas were also delicious and comes with guac! Highly recommend.

The food came out very quickly, but once the restaurant  got busier we saw our server less and less. It took about 30mins to get someone to bring our check to the table. The food was decent at best and the drinks we okay. Overall It's a good inexpensive place for a quick happy hour.

Dope spot to have some frozen margaritas and tasty Mexican food. Right on the popular U street in DC, where you can find the next spot after eating. The prices are pretty good, you won’t feel like you broke the bank. The staff and bartenders were friendly and attentive.

I came here for dinner on a Friday night and had a good experience! It wasn't too crowded and we were easily able to get a table for two. We got one of the combination platter (I think it was 27) and it was a good way to try a variety of the food and it was plenty for 2 people! They also have a good variety of drinks. Everything tasted pretty good, it's a good option if you're looking for Ethiopian food in the area.

Almost everything about the food is amazing, ranging from taste to portion to variety. My friend and I went to Shenandoah National Park during the day for some pretty intense hiking so we went into Dukem hungry for food. I had never been there prior to such, so I could not relate to anything mentioned in some other reviews in which people had mentioned how the portions had gotten smaller either due to inflation or change of management, but there was definitely enough food for the two of us. We got one of the combination platters, and some samosas. There was so much meat and veggies that we had to use extra injera for such. The only reason I am giving the place a 4 instead of a 5 star is due to the cleanliness. Some people mentioned flies, and I experienced such as well. Our table was also very sticky and required some additional cleaning prior to us being able to dine. When my friend and I went there, there was nobody else, maybe because it was early dinner time, so once again, I cannot relate too much with the service complaints. I have been to a couple of Ethiopian restaurants around the area, and I will recommend Dukem because it is one of those "hole in the wall" places where you can rely on for good food despite potential problems elsewhere. It doesn't look as fancy, but it has quite a bit of cultural presentation and representation, and that always matters more.

This place is a DC treasure! Located on U street in the unofficial little Ethiopia. I enjoyed the juicy lamb tibs with a small tomato salad. It’s was so flavorful! I hadn’t eaten here before though I had intended too several times. After hearing the owner passed away, it gave me more reason to enjoy a meal and pay my respects.

This Ethiopian restaurant was worth the travel from Miami. I tried the vegetarian combo platter, and it was absolutely sensational. I devoured the whole thing, and everything was delicious and spiced, perfectly portioned, and wonderfully presented. The staff is super friendly, and the food is outstanding. This is a family owned restaurant with lots of family values. You will not regret coming to this amazing spot.

I have been a loyal customer of Dukem for the last decade. Dukem was the first Ethiopian restaurant I visited when I lived to DC over a decade ago - and till date the only one I patronize. Friends, colleagues, visiting relatives - we bring everyone to Dukem.

For the first time - Service was atrocious! Beyond reprehensible. My brother and I walked in and the waitress ignored us for 10-15 minutes ( while all the Caucasian customers were served) until I requested a menu.

1 -We ordered a beer, a tea and a vegetarian platter. My brother got his beer but my tea never came - 15 minutes later ( and after asking 2x) - I was informed that they were out of tea. Would have been nice to know so that I could have ordered another beverage.

2- I asked for a side plate and some cutlery with my food. The waitress said she would bring it but didn’t - I asked again and then a third time. By this time we were 70% done with our food. The fourth time I walked up to the bar and asked again - she finally brought it out begrudgingly. All this while the other Caucasian tables around us were being served and asked if they needed anything / we were ignored.

3- finally after waiting for another 20 minutes, we paid the bill at the counter - only for the hostess who had been extremely rude until then to charge a mandatory 18% service charge . I’m not sure if this is a rule but their service did not warrant 18% and it was not communicated ahead of time. At this time we didn’t want to waste any more time there and we left ( with a very bitter taste from the whole situation)

It’s a shame - because the food was exceptional as always . I never experienced such blatant disregard and such terrible racial profiling at an establishment. It’s a shame it was at DUKEM

Had an absolute lovely time! The food was on point and the staff was super friendly from the get go. We were celebrating our anniversary and they were very accommodating. We had the seared tuna and a very tasty beet salad. The fry cake dessert was scrumptious.

Of course you go for the bourbon and they didn't disappoint. Some stuff we were looking for were out, but Matt was able to suggest similar bourbons that were awesome!

If you want to have a great time and try hard to find bourbon, stop by!

What an Amazing Whiskey Collection!! We had a night out of drinks here with our friend who was visiting us and we absolutely loved the place and the collection of whiskeys and bourbon and so many other stuff! The bar tenders are so friendly and knowledgeable about everything! I said I love fruity cocktails with either Gin or Vodka and instant cocktails were created!

Must visit in DC

Jack Rose offers an endless variety of whiskeys and bourbons.

I honestly recommend letting the bartenders know what you like, including geographic distillery locations and if you prefer single or double malt and let them do the rest.

I love the unique and exquisite options and the presentation is second to none.

I highly recommend visiting Jack Rose if you are looking for a gentleman's watering hole.

Every time I'm in DC I find an excuse to come here. The food is excellent but this is the best Bourbon bar in America for variety, with pretty decent prices as well. It's hands down my favorite bar.

The rooftop is cool and open while the saloon area is dark and cozy. The staff is extremely knowledgeable about bourbon and the bartenders are amazing.

You must go here if you enjoy bourbon.

One of the best collections of Scotch Malt Whisky Society on the east coast, along with lots of other unique bottles with a real range in prices. The staff are eternally nice and thoughtful, and will happily help you find the right pour for your tastes. A date night favorite if whiskey is your thing.

One of the best stakes I have tried in DC! I went for brunch, prices are fair, really good portion, very tasty food, I loved the drinks and our waitress was super nice. We sat outside, though you can opt to sit inside as well. Really good experience, I have been to the one 14th st so was good to visit this location.
My mom and I had a craving for pizza and stopped in. My mom loved her pizza and I ended up getting the meatball sub. I’d have photos but I ate it in about five seconds.

Have been for brunch and for dinner during the pandemic. They have set up a lot of extra tables that are well-distanced and it feels very safe and comfortable. The food, as always, is great. You can make a reservation online - which may be smart for dinner time on the weekends - but I’ve always been able to find a table at other times.

I’ve also found that their pizza is much better eaten in person than takeaway. Brunch food is really good, would give it 8/10. Try the hash if you can!

Overpriced, crust on bottom seemed undercooked.  Dine in might be better. In their defense, most higher end pizza take out I've had during the pandemic has been pretty lackluster. Sauce seemed a bit too sweet for my taste. The employee who gave me my order was nice.

When my family and I got there it was 11:35, that particular day they opened at 11:30. When we arrived the doors were locked so we looked down at the kitchen where there were woman cooking . We knocked and told them we wanted to dine in the lady was so rude and nasty saying well we not open nobody upstairs and closed the door in my face ! worst experience at this red rocks I suggest everyone go to the one on H street where the customer service is excellent
